gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 114, Warriors 110
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Golden State, 114-110. For Minnesota, Anthony Edwards led the way with 23 points (four 3PM), six rebounds, and eight assists while aided by Naz Reid (20 points, 12 rebounds, two blocks) and Rudy Gobert (17 points, 12 rebounds) in the victory. Stephen Curry finished with 31 points (five 3PM) and four rebounds with Klay Thompson adding 16 points and three rebounds for Golden State in the losing effort. Minnesota improves to 49-22, while Golden State moves to 36-34 in the loss.
